# The task

Produce two groups:

**Adjacent (4-5)** — Companies very similar to what the user already tracks. Same category, similar stage, similar product surface. Obvious gap-fillers the user likely just hasn't gotten around to.

**Discovery (4-5)** — Net-new companies the user might not know. Emerging names, recent breakouts, notable scale-ups, strong niche players in the user's domain. Ground each one in something recent (funding round, product launch, hiring surge) — not just "company exists and is hiring".

## For each company, emit

- **name** — canonical company name
- **careers_url** — the real, verified careers page URL (not a guessed domain)
- **platform_guess** — one of `greenhouse`, `ashby`, `lever`, `workday`, `smartrecruiters`, `custom`. Pick `custom` if you're unsure or if the company uses their own careers site (e.g. Amazon, Microsoft, Google, Apple).
- **why_relevant** — ONE concise sentence. Cite the specific reason this candidate would care (e.g. "your AI-infra PM experience maps directly to their 40-person Platform team who just raised Series C").

## Output — JSON only, no prose, no markdown fences

```json
{
  "suggestions": [
    {
      "source": "adjacent",
      "name": "Pinecone",
      "careers_url": "https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/pinecone",
